      "content": "it just feels like a cycle that never ends. the more i try to be better, the more i mess up, and the more i see the light go out of their eyes when i fail. sometimes i think the only way i can actually be selfless is to just... stop being a burden to them. like, if i wasnt here, they could finally just breathe and be kids without worrying about me. it almost feels like the only kind thing left to do.",
